import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['delay'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7, edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['delay'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Delay (minutes)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.boxplot(data['distance'])
    avg_distance = data['distance'].mean()
    ax.axhline(avg_distance, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Distance: {avg_distance:.2f}')
    plt.xlabel('Flights')
    plt.ylabel('Distance')
    plt.title('What is the average distance of flights?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    origin_counts = data['origin'].value_counts()
    destination_counts = data['destination'].value_counts()

    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.bar(origin_counts.index, origin_counts.values, label='Origin', alpha=0.5)
    ax.bar(destination_counts.index, destination_counts.values, label='Destination', alpha=0.5)
    ax.set_xlabel('Airport')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Flights')
    ax.set_title('What is the most common origin and destination for flights?')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['distance'], data['delay'])
    plt.xlabel('Distance')
    plt.ylabel('Delay')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between delay time and distance?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    data['date_only'] = data['date'].dt.date
    date_counts = data['date_only'].value_counts().sort_index()
    
    plt.plot(date_counts.index, date_counts.values)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of flight dates?")
    plt.xlabel("Date")
    plt.ylabel("Number of Flights")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
